<subSubSection id="0B9B9127ED992986409A74C2103BFC31" pageId="482" pageNumber="483" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="B9779DA3F64DB03848F6BA2D89BEF6A4" pageId="482" pageNumber="483">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F0A2C7455ADFE01CDABC710991D67430" pageId="482" pageNumber="483">This species ranges from southeastern Virginia (Norfolk, Robert L. Davidson pers. comm. 2012) to eastern Oklahoma, south to southeastern Texas and southwestern Florida [see Erwin 1970a: Fig. 366]. The records from New York (LeConte 1846b: 203), New Jersey (Smith 1910: 212), southeastern Iowa (King 1914: 322; Hendrickson 1930: 94), and Missouri (Summers 1873: 133) need confirmation.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
